{"lemma":"باسِط","slug":"باسِط","root":"ب.س.ط","root_slug":"ب-س-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-س-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"باسِط","root":"بسط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2543"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%B7"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"active participle of بَسَطَ (basaṭa, “to extend, to stretch”)","tags":["active","form-i","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"extensor (causing the joint to extend)","tags":["form-i","participle"],"examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: قَابِض (qābiḍ)"},{"text":"عَضَلَة بَاسِطَة","english":"an extensor muscle"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of بَسَطَ (basaṭa, “to extend, to stretch”)."},"ipa":["/baː.sitˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2543","headword_ar":"بَاسِطٌ","root":"bsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa","text_ar":"بَسَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  It is said in the Kur [vi. 93],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlmalaAy^ikapu baAsiTuwA A^ayodiyhimo","text_ar":"وَالمَلَايِكَةُ بَاسِطُوا اَيْدِيهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The angels being made to have dominion"},{"kind":"text","text":"over them"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by absolute force and power"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) And again, in the Kur [xiii. 15],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaAsiTi kaf~ayohi","text_ar":"كَبَاسِطِ كَفَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY AlmaA='i liyaboluga","text_ar":"اـِلَى المَا=ءِ لِيَبْلُغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the supplicator of water, making a sign to it [with his two hands], in order that it may [reach his mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so] answer his prayer; (K, * TA;) or, but it will not answer his prayer. (O, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAsiTu","text_ar":"البَاسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God, who amplifies, or enlarges, or makes ample or plentiful, the means of subsistence, to whomsoever He will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) by his liberality and his mercy: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or who diffuses (yabosuTu) the souls in the bodies at the time of [their] being animated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N baAsiTN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ بَاسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that is distant from the herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasturage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but less so than what is termed muTolibN."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamosN baAsiTN","text_ar":"خَمْسٌ بَاسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A difficult [journey of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosa","text_ar":"خِمْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e. of five days, whereof the second and third and fourth are without water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAy^iSN","text_ar":"بَايِصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sgh, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobapN baAsiTapN","text_ar":"عُقْبَةٌ بَاسِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISK, S, M, K [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabapN","text_ar":"عَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) (assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stage of a journey, or march or journey from one halting-place to another,] that is far, or distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or in which are two nights to the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sironaA","text_ar":"سِرْنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobapF baAsiTapF","text_ar":"عُقْبَةً بَاسِطَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We journeyed a stage, &c.,] that was far, or distant, or long"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISk, S, * TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiy~apN qaAmapN baAsiTapN","text_ar":"رَكِيَّةٌ قَامَةٌ بَاسِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the CK,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qAmapu bAsiTapN","text_ar":"قامَةُ باسِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a prefixed n. with its complement imperfectly decl., as though they made it determinate,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmapN wabasoTapN","text_ar":"قَامَةٌ وَبَسْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well measuring, or of the depth of, a man's stature and an arm's length"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.) AZ says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara Alr~ajulu qaAmapF baAsiTapF","text_ar":"حَفَرَ الرَّجُلُ قَامَةً بَاسِطَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man dug to the depth of his stature and his arm's length"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","M","ISk","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%B7/","headword_ar":"باسط","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=130390#a23960","body_html":"باسط<br>من (ب س ط) السار، والقاشر الشيء، والماد يده إلى المرء بما يحب أو يكره."}]}}